## Project requirements
- .NET 10
- ASP.NET Core Web API
- SQL Server
- Angular 20
- Clean Architecture
- Repository Pattern
- JWT Authentication
- xUnit

## Forbidden:

- Entity Framework
- Dapper
- MediatR


## Architecture Rules
- Enforce Clean Architecture strictly
- Domain layer is completely independent (NO EF Core, NO external libs)
- Application layer contains use cases and interfaces only
- Infrastructure layer implements all external concerns (DB, APIs, File system)
- API layer is thin: controllers only orchestrate Application layer

## Dependency Rules
- Domain -> no dependencies
- Application -> depends only on Domain
- Infrastructure -> depends on Application + Domain
- API -> depends on Application
-Tests

## Design Principles
- Follow SOLID strictly
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Avoid anemic domain models when possible
- Business logic must live in Domain layer
- Keep controllers thin.
- Put business logic in services.
- Use dependency injection

## Data Access
- Microsoft.Data.SqlClient
- ADO.NET only
- Async methods
- Parameterized queries

## Testing Requirements
- Domain logic MUST be unit tested
- Application use cases MUST be tested
- Use mocks for external dependencies
- Tests should follow AAA pattern (Arrange, Act, Assert)

## API Standards
- RESTful design
- Proper HTTP status codes
- DTOs must be used for input/output
- No domain entities exposed in API

## Error Handling
- Use custom domain exceptions
- Do not expose internal exceptions to API
- Centralized exception middleware required

## Performance & Scalability
- Avoid N+1 queries
- Use async/await everywhere in I/O operations
- Prefer pagination for all list endpoints

## Code Quality
- No "magic strings"
- No business logic in controllers
- Keep methods small and single responsibility
- Explicit over implicit code

## Interview Simulation Mode
- Code must reflect production-ready standards
- Avoid shortcuts or pseudo-code
- Assume system will scale to real enterprise usage